ASX-listed Birimian refers to the trading halt request dated 13 November 2018 and the request for voluntary suspension dated 15 November 2018. The company is still in the process of conducting a review of its activities and is not yet able to make an announcement in this respect. Accordingly, the company requests that its securities remain in voluntary suspension until the earlier of the commencement of trading on 14 December 2018 or until the release of an ASX announcement regarding the Company and its activities. Birimian is not aware of any reason why the voluntary suspension should not be granted
or any further information necessary to inform the market about the voluntary suspension.